Russell ate several candies on Halloween, and each day after Halloween ate 6 fewer candies than the day before. His candies lasted exactly five days, and he ate 100 candies in total. How many did he eat on the third day?

}

\textbf{Answer:} If we let $x$ stand for the number of candies eaten on the third day, then on the second day he ate $x+6$, on the first day he ate $x+12$, on the fourth day he ate $x-6$, and on the fifth day he ate $x-12$. In total $100 = (x+12) + (x+6) + x + (x-6) + (x-12)$, and so $100 = 5x$, and thus he ate $\boxed{20}$ candies on the third day.
